      <section role="ITEM">
        <title>Bank Invoice Payment - Edit Transactions</title>

        <para role="TEXT">This option allows a Bank Invoice to be completed or
        modified.</para>

        <para role="TEXT">When selected, this option will present a list of
        Bank Invoices that have been prepared and saved by customer users, but
        not yet submitted because the input user either did not try to submit
        or had insufficient privileges.</para>

        <para role="TEXT">Click in the <emphasis role="bold">System
        Id</emphasis> column to open a message for further editing.</para>
      </section>

      <section role="ITEM">
        <title>Bank Invoice Payment - Retrieve Unsigned</title>

        <para role="TEXT">This option allows a Bank Invoice to be submitted by
        an authorised user.</para>

        <para role="TEXT">When selected, this option will present a list of
        Bank Invoices that have been prepared and saved by customer users, but
        have not been successfully submitted to the bank because the user had
        insufficient privileges. Records that were simply saved with no
        attempt to submit them are not included.</para>

        <para role="TEXT">Click in the <guilabel moreinfo="none">System
        Id</guilabel><guilabel moreinfo="none"> </guilabel>column to open the
        message in a non-editable mode, in order to review the data and
        perform the submission.</para>

        <para role="TEXT">If you have sufficient authorisation in your
        profile, you can submit multiple records in a single operation
        directly from the list. Each record in the list has a check box which
        you tick to select it. A button at the end of the page submits all the
        selected records.</para>

        <para role="TEXT">The result of the action is then returned, with a
        list of records that have now been successfully sent to the clients,
        together with a list of records that have again failed validation. The
        updated list of unsigned records is then also displayed.</para>
      </section>
